13 packaged in a container not larger than three hundred seventy-five
14 (375) milliliters. Such term shall include but not be limited to
15 the beverage popularly known as a "wine cooler";
16 40. 41. "Mixed beverages" means one or more servings of a
17 beverage composed in whole or in part of an alcoholic beverage in a
18 sealed or unsealed container of any legal size for consumption on
19 the premises where served or sold by the holder of a mixed beverage,
20 beer and wine, caterer, public event, charitable event or special
21 event license; provided, that a beer, cider, or wine mixed with
22 ingredients nonalcoholic in nature including, but not limited to,
23 water, juice, sugar, fruits, or vegetables and sold by a small
24 brewer, brewpub, small farm winery, or winemaker, shall not be
